WEBVTT

00:07.441 --> 00:08.041
‐ Previously
on "The Purge"...

00:09.176 --> 00:11.945
‐ Whoever's in my house,
you're not getting out alive.

00:11.979 --> 00:14.248
‐ What have I done
to make you hate me so much?

00:14.281 --> 00:15.849
‐ You killed my wife.

00:15.883 --> 00:17.618
I'm the one
that's gonna kill you.

00:17.651 --> 00:19.019
‐ What about
the backup chamber?

00:19.052 --> 00:19.953
Can you extend the range
on that?

00:19.987 --> 00:22.022
‐ You built two?
‐ Just in case.

00:22.055 --> 00:24.258
‐ I need another favor.
‐ [sighs]

00:24.291 --> 00:26.426
Wait, he doesn't know?

00:26.460 --> 00:29.062
‐ He knows that I'm working
with the Foundation.

00:29.096 --> 00:31.031
He just doesn't know
the endgame.

00:31.064 --> 00:33.867
‐ Case 20854 is now closed.

00:33.901 --> 00:36.603
Execution will be carried out
on the next Purge Night.

00:36.637 --> 00:38.105
‐ Let's go get our boy.

00:38.138 --> 00:40.140
‐ Who's going hunting
with me tonight?

00:40.173 --> 00:41.241
[blade plunges]

00:41.275 --> 00:43.110
[device beeps]
‐ What did you do?

00:43.143 --> 00:44.077
[tires squealing]

00:47.714 --> 00:50.117
‐ Listen up‐‐another Purge
is about to begin.

00:50.150 --> 00:52.452
Remember, there's a tagged
suspect on the loose.

00:52.486 --> 00:55.289
[sirens blaring]

00:55.322 --> 00:59.159
[dramatic music]

00:59.192 --> 01:02.362
‐ [laughing]

01:02.396 --> 01:05.365
[all chattering]

01:05.399 --> 01:07.968
All right, boys and girls!

01:08.001 --> 01:10.003
Let's have some quiet time now

01:10.037 --> 01:12.472
and think about our feelings.

01:12.506 --> 01:13.740
[giggles]

01:13.774 --> 01:18.011
So I've been having
some worries lately...

01:18.045 --> 01:20.180
and worries can be hard
to talk about,

01:20.213 --> 01:22.049
even for grown‐ups.

01:22.082 --> 01:24.785
That's why, in America,
we have a holiday

01:24.818 --> 01:27.721
that helps people
get their worries out.

01:27.754 --> 01:30.490
Do any of you know
what it's called?

01:31.858 --> 01:33.694
Zoe...

01:33.727 --> 01:36.663
something tells me you know.

01:36.697 --> 01:38.432
‐ The Purge?

01:38.465 --> 01:40.434
‐ That's right.

01:40.467 --> 01:43.170
The Purge allows grown‐ups

01:43.203 --> 01:45.439
to deal with their bad feelings

01:45.472 --> 01:48.742
by giving them one night
to do whatever they want.

01:48.775 --> 01:50.611
‐ They can stay up
as late as they want?

01:50.644 --> 01:53.447
‐ All night.
[all gasp]

01:53.480 --> 01:55.415
‐ Can they kill people?

01:55.449 --> 01:58.452
[all gasp, murmur]

01:58.485 --> 02:01.288
‐ Yes, they can.

02:01.321 --> 02:03.090
[giggles]

02:03.123 --> 02:06.526
The Purge
gives your mommies and daddies

02:06.560 --> 02:08.795
the freedom
to accomplish things

02:08.829 --> 02:11.298
they never thought possible.
[giggles]

02:11.331 --> 02:13.233
‐ What if something happens
to my mom

02:13.266 --> 02:15.168
or my little brother?

02:15.202 --> 02:18.972
‐ Oh, Zoe.
[giggles]

02:19.006 --> 02:22.275
Whatever happens...

02:22.309 --> 02:26.446
you and your brother
will be perfectly safe.

02:26.480 --> 02:30.550
And if your mommy or daddy
decide to Purge,

02:30.584 --> 02:32.753
mm, that's their decision.

02:32.786 --> 02:35.856
That is their right
as Americans.

02:35.889 --> 02:39.126
You know how sometimes
you may want to scream or cry

02:39.159 --> 02:42.396
or punch a pillow
because you are so angry?

02:42.429 --> 02:45.065
Well, the Purge
is just like that.

02:45.098 --> 02:47.367
But for adults only,
so there's no reason...

02:47.401 --> 02:48.468
[voice fades]

02:48.502 --> 02:50.837
‐ Ben! Ben!

02:50.871 --> 02:53.006
Ben!

02:53.040 --> 02:54.474
[chuckles]

02:54.508 --> 02:56.777
It's time for lunch, honey.

02:56.810 --> 02:58.345
What are you watching?

02:58.378 --> 03:02.449
‐ Blessed be
our New Founding Fathers

03:02.482 --> 03:04.418
and America...

03:04.451 --> 03:07.220
a nation reborn.

03:07.254 --> 03:10.257
[all laughing]

03:10.290 --> 03:13.260
[dark music]

03:13.293 --> 03:17.264
♪ ♪

03:17.297 --> 03:18.598
[static crackling]

03:18.632 --> 03:21.568
[dramatic music]

03:21.601 --> 03:28.508
♪ ♪

03:33.346 --> 03:37.284
[suspenseful music]

03:37.317 --> 03:39.619
‐ Smile, Turner.

03:39.653 --> 03:42.789
Purge has officially started.

03:42.823 --> 03:44.458
It's time to celebrate.

03:44.491 --> 03:47.160
‐ Please, Ben,
just let Scott go.

03:47.194 --> 03:48.395
‐ [whimpering]

03:48.428 --> 03:52.299
‐ This is between you and me.

03:52.332 --> 03:53.867
‐ You're right.

03:53.900 --> 03:55.502
‐ No.
No, please.

03:55.535 --> 03:57.237
Please don't do this.

03:57.270 --> 03:58.672
[tape slams]
Please!

03:58.705 --> 04:00.540
‐ Look, I get it, man.

04:00.574 --> 04:03.477
You've been through a lot
this year.

04:03.510 --> 04:05.512
We‐‐we could
still get you help.

04:05.545 --> 04:07.981
‐ Oh, I know
it seems scary now...

04:08.014 --> 04:10.317
‐ [whimpering]

04:10.350 --> 04:12.652
‐ But I'm trying
to give you a gift.

04:12.686 --> 04:14.454
♪ ♪

04:14.488 --> 04:16.656
So here's the deal‐‐

04:16.690 --> 04:20.527
if you finally pop
your cherry...

04:20.560 --> 04:22.529
and kill little Scotty here...

04:22.562 --> 04:24.498
‐ [whimpering]

04:24.531 --> 04:26.833
‐ I'll let you live.

04:26.867 --> 04:28.702
So, either one
of you dies...

04:28.735 --> 04:30.203
♪ ♪

04:30.237 --> 04:33.340
Or both of you die.

04:33.373 --> 04:35.509
Your choice, bruh.

04:35.542 --> 04:40.213
♪ ♪

04:40.247 --> 04:43.216
[sirens wailing,
explosions]

04:43.250 --> 04:45.752
[gunfire, horns honking]

04:45.786 --> 04:49.356
[indistinct chatter]

04:49.389 --> 04:51.258
‐ I know
it's Purge Night, people,

04:51.291 --> 04:53.960
but remember, Esme Carmona
is our number‐one priority.

04:53.994 --> 04:56.696
[computer chirping]

04:56.730 --> 04:58.765
[engine rumbling]

04:58.799 --> 05:05.338
♪ ♪

05:06.706 --> 05:08.308
[engine stops]

05:08.341 --> 05:14.714
♪ ♪

05:14.748 --> 05:16.449
‐ Okay.

05:16.483 --> 05:20.654
♪ ♪

05:20.687 --> 05:23.657
‐ About time.
Starting to wonder.

05:23.690 --> 05:25.859
[indistinct chatter]

05:25.892 --> 05:27.460
[lock snaps]

05:27.494 --> 05:31.865
[indistinct chatter]

05:31.898 --> 05:33.667
‐ Transfer the money
before the sirens,

05:33.700 --> 05:36.002
or I will send the photos
to everyone in your contacts.

05:36.036 --> 05:37.771
[computers chirping]

05:37.804 --> 05:39.739
‐ [Speaking Korean]

05:39.773 --> 05:40.974
‐ Yo, Skye.

05:41.007 --> 05:42.576
Looks like CryptoCash
is the winner.

05:42.609 --> 05:43.877
I'm almost in.
‐ Sweet.

05:43.910 --> 05:46.613
Keep an eye on your event logs.

05:46.646 --> 05:48.849
‐ So much crime,
so little space.

05:48.882 --> 05:51.451
‐ Foundation makes more
on Purge than we do all year.

05:51.484 --> 05:52.919
So final warning:

05:52.953 --> 05:55.655
I think your plan's insane.

05:55.689 --> 05:58.658
‐ Noted.
‐ But I like insane.

05:58.692 --> 06:00.126
We'll be waiting outside
for you to send the footage.

06:00.160 --> 06:02.829
Then we'll blast it
to every screen we can access.

06:02.863 --> 06:04.531
But based on what you told me,

06:04.564 --> 06:06.600
in order to get into
the surveillance center,

06:06.633 --> 06:08.235
I need to
turn you into a ghost.

06:08.268 --> 06:10.837
[keys clacking]
‐ What does that mean?

06:10.871 --> 06:12.706
‐ You'll see.

06:12.739 --> 06:15.709
[sinister music]

06:15.742 --> 06:22.782
♪ ♪

06:25.252 --> 06:26.720
‐ Have you ever Purged before?

06:26.753 --> 06:28.355
‐ Yeah, once in college.

06:28.388 --> 06:30.991
‐ Wait, you have?

06:31.024 --> 06:34.327
‐ Um...
‐ What's wrong?

06:34.361 --> 06:35.829
‐ Nothing, Clint.

06:35.862 --> 06:39.866
Uh, just‐‐
‐ Purge jitters, that's all.

06:39.900 --> 06:41.301
Let's go.

06:41.334 --> 06:43.336
[indistinct chatter]

06:43.370 --> 06:46.506
[truck door closes,
engine turns over]

06:46.539 --> 06:49.342
[engine revving]

06:49.376 --> 06:50.977
[tires squeal]

06:51.011 --> 06:52.512
♪ ♪

06:52.545 --> 06:55.548
[alarm wailing]

06:57.450 --> 07:00.487
Hey, they got past
the outer door.

07:00.520 --> 07:01.454
[wailing stops]

07:01.488 --> 07:02.555
‐ Look, we tried to
reason with them.

07:02.589 --> 07:04.658
If we have to fight back,
it'll be self‐defense.

07:04.691 --> 07:06.026
‐ Hey, hey, hey,
they're making a move.

07:06.059 --> 07:07.560
Do you see this?

07:07.594 --> 07:09.429
♪ ♪

07:09.462 --> 07:12.065
‐ Move.

07:12.098 --> 07:15.135
[bottles clinking]

07:15.168 --> 07:17.037
♪ ♪

07:17.070 --> 07:19.572
‐ Babe, just promise me
that no matter what happens

07:19.606 --> 07:21.675
that we won't
turn into one of them.

07:21.708 --> 07:24.010
♪ ♪

07:24.044 --> 07:25.912
‐ Okay.
‐ All right.

07:25.946 --> 07:28.782
[suspenseful music]

07:28.815 --> 07:30.450
‐ Come on.

07:30.483 --> 07:33.753
♪ ♪

07:33.787 --> 07:35.455
[lighter flicks]

07:35.488 --> 07:42.529
♪ ♪

07:45.598 --> 07:47.701
[gun cocks]

07:47.734 --> 07:49.703
♪ ♪

07:49.736 --> 07:51.905
‐ This place fireproof?
‐ As much as possible.

07:51.938 --> 07:54.140
♪ ♪

07:54.174 --> 07:55.642
‐ [screams]
‐ Get back!

07:55.675 --> 07:57.444
Stay back!

07:57.477 --> 08:03.083
♪ ♪

08:03.116 --> 08:04.884
‐ We're on borrowed time
in here!

08:04.918 --> 08:06.486
They're gonna smoke us out!

08:06.519 --> 08:08.555
[buzzer blares]

08:08.588 --> 08:11.391
♪ ♪

08:11.424 --> 08:13.326
‐ Prisoners for tonight's hunt
have landed.

08:13.360 --> 08:14.594
‐ Copy that.

08:14.627 --> 08:16.062
[brakes squeak]

08:16.096 --> 08:18.131
[air hisses,
door creaks open]

08:18.164 --> 08:22.135
♪ ♪

08:22.168 --> 08:24.037
‐ Nice night for a hunt.

08:24.070 --> 08:30.310
♪ ♪

08:30.343 --> 08:32.078
Come on, let's go.

08:32.112 --> 08:33.513
♪ ♪

08:33.546 --> 08:34.681
‐ What's this?

08:34.714 --> 08:36.783
I thought we were supposed to
be getting auctioned off?

08:36.816 --> 08:37.884
‐ Go.

08:37.917 --> 08:41.121
‐ Hey, what we supposed to do
out here all alone?

08:41.154 --> 08:43.456
‐ Die.
Now move it.

08:43.490 --> 08:45.692
[indistinct chatter]

08:45.725 --> 08:47.794
[chains jingling]

08:47.827 --> 08:50.163
Move. Move.

08:50.196 --> 08:53.033
♪ ♪

08:53.066 --> 08:55.802
Come on, go!

08:55.835 --> 08:58.104
‐ Hey, hey,
we're still chained up.

08:58.138 --> 08:59.239
How are we supposed
to fight back?

08:59.272 --> 09:01.608
‐ They don't want us
to fight back.

09:01.641 --> 09:03.109
They sold us
to a bunch of rich assholes

09:03.143 --> 09:04.711
who want to Purge
without the danger.

09:04.744 --> 09:06.012
‐ What?

09:06.046 --> 09:07.380
‐ It doesn't have to end
like this.

09:07.414 --> 09:08.748
I got a friend
who's gonna get us out of here.

09:08.782 --> 09:11.451
‐ And how do we know
this friend is gonna show up?

09:11.484 --> 09:12.952
‐ Ryan's never
let me down before.

09:12.986 --> 09:13.820
You got to trust me.

09:13.853 --> 09:16.089
We all have to stick together,

09:16.122 --> 09:19.059
or we're not gonna make it
through the night, okay?

09:19.092 --> 09:19.893
‐ Yeah, sure.

09:19.926 --> 09:22.562
‐ Officers, move them forward!

09:22.595 --> 09:24.230
[indistinct radio chatter]

09:24.264 --> 09:25.865
‐ Here's your head start.

09:25.899 --> 09:28.001
‐ Follow me.
Come on, let's go.

09:31.571 --> 09:33.540
‐ Welcome to the hunt.

09:33.573 --> 09:36.543
[festive music playing
over speakers]

09:36.576 --> 09:38.645
♪ ♪

09:38.678 --> 09:41.147
‐ Reservation for Dixon
plus two.

09:41.181 --> 09:43.416
‐ Thank you for your donation.

09:43.450 --> 09:46.653
[indistinct chatter,
dishware clinks]

09:46.686 --> 09:47.987
♪ ♪

09:48.021 --> 09:50.990
[no audible dialogue]

09:51.024 --> 09:58.031
♪ ♪

09:59.933 --> 10:02.869
‐ So glad we dressed
for the occasion.

10:02.902 --> 10:04.838
‐ We paid our admission
like everybody else,

10:04.871 --> 10:06.539
so they can't complain.

10:08.208 --> 10:10.777
‐ [chuckles]
Ladies and gentlemen,

10:10.810 --> 10:13.880
we have a surprise
for all of you.

10:13.913 --> 10:15.615
Tonight's sponsor‐‐

10:15.648 --> 10:18.685
the Daughters of the NFFA‐‐

10:18.718 --> 10:21.621
have planned a special treat.

10:21.654 --> 10:24.958
In honor of our heritage
and our traditions

10:24.991 --> 10:28.061
that trace back
over 200 years‐‐

10:28.094 --> 10:31.931
which form the bedrock
of the NFFA‐‐

10:31.965 --> 10:35.902
tonight's hunt
will consist only...

10:35.969 --> 10:39.739
of weapons used
by our ancestors.

10:39.772 --> 10:42.175
[all gasp]
‐ Wow!

10:42.208 --> 10:44.310
[applause]

10:44.344 --> 10:48.081
‐ They got to be kidding.
‐ This is so fucked up.

10:48.114 --> 10:51.117
[indistinct chatter]

10:53.853 --> 10:56.122
‐ Careful with this one, sir.

10:57.724 --> 10:59.759
‐ Here you go.

10:59.792 --> 11:01.761
‐ You can pick your weapon up
at the coat check

11:01.794 --> 11:03.263
on your way out, sir.

11:03.296 --> 11:08.134
♪ ♪

11:08.168 --> 11:11.004
‐ Hey, we got more firepower
in the Humvee,

11:11.037 --> 11:12.305
so let's just make do.

11:12.338 --> 11:14.741
‐ Yeah, but what if we have to
take some of these assholes out

11:14.774 --> 11:15.875
in the process?

11:15.909 --> 11:18.278
‐ It's not ideal, but I'm not
gonna shed a tear over it.

11:18.311 --> 11:20.680
Are you?
‐ No way.

11:20.713 --> 11:22.815
[lively classical music
playing]

11:22.849 --> 11:24.918
‐ Let's make our way
up front.

11:24.951 --> 11:28.021
♪ ♪

11:28.054 --> 11:30.657
‐ Thank you.

11:30.690 --> 11:33.660
[suspenseful music]

11:33.693 --> 11:35.195
♪ ♪

11:35.228 --> 11:37.063
‐ Everybody grab one.

11:37.096 --> 11:39.065
‐ Clint, our fight
is with Marcus.

11:39.098 --> 11:41.367
There's other people in there.
‐ That's not my problem.

11:41.401 --> 11:43.102
‐ You're talking
about burning them alive!

11:43.136 --> 11:45.171
‐ Yeah, I am.

11:45.205 --> 11:47.907
They tried to burn you.
What's the problem?

11:47.941 --> 11:51.778
♪ ♪

11:51.811 --> 11:54.113
Unless you still have feelings
for Michelle.

11:54.147 --> 11:55.882
♪ ♪

11:55.915 --> 11:57.183
‐ No, I don't.

11:57.217 --> 11:59.252
[door clattering]

11:59.285 --> 12:03.056
♪ ♪

12:03.089 --> 12:04.791
[door clangs]

12:04.824 --> 12:07.860
♪ ♪

12:07.894 --> 12:10.663
‐ If you're sending people out,
we'll hold our fire!

12:10.697 --> 12:14.901
♪ ♪

12:14.934 --> 12:17.237
Go check it out,
Mr. Bleeding Heart.

12:17.270 --> 12:19.205
Tell them they can
send the rest out safely

12:19.239 --> 12:20.306
if they give us Marcus.

12:20.340 --> 12:22.308
‐ No. No.

12:22.342 --> 12:23.142
[gun cocks]

12:23.176 --> 12:24.944
Clint, don't!

12:24.978 --> 12:26.846
‐ It's okay.
‐ Jesus, Clint.

12:26.879 --> 12:29.148
‐ I'll go.
I'll go.

12:29.182 --> 12:31.184
♪ ♪

12:31.217 --> 12:33.987
‐ That's what I like to hear.

12:34.020 --> 12:35.154
Move.

12:35.188 --> 12:41.194
♪ ♪

12:43.196 --> 12:46.032
I'll help you get over
your Purge jitters.

12:46.065 --> 12:53.072
♪ ♪

13:27.507 --> 13:29.208
‐ Marcus?

13:29.242 --> 13:31.077
♪ ♪

13:31.110 --> 13:32.912
Michelle?

13:32.945 --> 13:38.251
♪ ♪

13:38.284 --> 13:40.787
I'm here to cut you guys
a deal.

13:42.455 --> 13:44.223
[screams]

13:44.257 --> 13:47.060
[grunts]
Guys, help me!

13:47.093 --> 13:49.896
Guys, help me!

13:49.929 --> 13:51.831
[grunting]
‐ Sam!

13:51.864 --> 13:53.399
‐ [grunts]
Aah!

13:59.339 --> 13:59.539
‐ [screams]

14:00.940 --> 14:02.141
[panting]
Please!

14:02.175 --> 14:03.743
P‐please don't Purge me!

14:03.776 --> 14:06.012
Please!
[grunting, gasping]

14:06.045 --> 14:07.847
Holy shit!
[yelps]

14:07.880 --> 14:10.049
‐ I'm not gonna Purge you, Sam.

14:10.083 --> 14:11.784
I was forced
to pull the trigger

14:11.818 --> 14:14.354
a lot of years ago,
and that shit sticks with you.

14:14.387 --> 14:15.888
[tense music]

14:15.922 --> 14:17.123
Pour this on there.
‐ Okay.

14:17.156 --> 14:19.892
‐ Okay, and then put it
on that laceration.

14:19.926 --> 14:21.961
♪ ♪

14:21.994 --> 14:25.264
‐ No, wait.
[hollers, grunts]

14:25.298 --> 14:27.033
[panting]
Look...

14:27.066 --> 14:28.935
♪ ♪

14:28.968 --> 14:31.137
This‐‐this whole thing
has gotten way out of hand.

14:31.170 --> 14:33.940
‐ Yeah?
No shit.

14:33.973 --> 14:38.144
‐ Clint wants
to smoke you guys out.

14:38.177 --> 14:41.047
He won't stop
until you're dead.

14:41.080 --> 14:42.014
‐ I hate to say it, Marcus,

14:42.048 --> 14:44.217
but maybe it's time
for us to change tactics.

14:44.250 --> 14:46.419
‐ Honey, if we fight fire
with fire, then we lose,

14:46.452 --> 14:48.254
and that's not who we are.

14:48.287 --> 14:49.956
There's got to be another way.

14:49.989 --> 14:51.491
Now...

14:51.524 --> 14:53.459
this is gonna hurt like shit.

14:53.493 --> 14:55.328
‐ [whimpers]

14:55.361 --> 14:57.897
[grunts, screams]

14:57.930 --> 14:59.499
‐ [grunts]

14:59.532 --> 15:01.401
‐ I told you,
I'm not gonna do it.

15:01.434 --> 15:03.102
I'm not a killer, man.

15:03.136 --> 15:04.437
‐ No...

15:04.470 --> 15:06.406
‐ [grunts, whimpers]

15:06.439 --> 15:09.375
‐ But you will be.

15:09.409 --> 15:10.843
‐ No, please.
Come on, man.

15:10.877 --> 15:13.246
Ah, come on!
[both grunt]

15:13.279 --> 15:15.281
Let me go of me, man, please!

15:15.314 --> 15:17.116
[hollers]

15:17.150 --> 15:18.851
[panting]

15:18.885 --> 15:20.820
No!
‐ No, no, no.

15:20.853 --> 15:22.488
‐ Oh, shit. Ben...

15:22.522 --> 15:24.590
‐ Do it...
‐ Please don't.

15:24.624 --> 15:28.594
‐ Or I will fucking Purge you.

15:28.628 --> 15:30.963
‐ I can't, I can't‐‐
[hollers] No, no, no, no!

15:30.997 --> 15:32.165
[whimpers]
No!

15:32.198 --> 15:35.067
[screaming]

15:35.101 --> 15:37.336
No!

15:37.370 --> 15:39.305
[screams]

15:39.338 --> 15:41.607
[whimpering]
‐ [grunting]

15:41.641 --> 15:43.276
‐ [hollers]

15:43.309 --> 15:46.279
[hyperventilating]
‐ [gasping]

15:46.312 --> 15:49.282
[dark music]

15:49.315 --> 15:52.318
♪ ♪

15:52.351 --> 15:54.253
You did it.

15:54.287 --> 15:55.955
You did it, man!

15:55.988 --> 15:58.024
[laughs]

15:58.057 --> 16:01.027
Oh...
[breathing deeply]

16:01.060 --> 16:08.067
♪ ♪

16:14.040 --> 16:17.076
[indistinct chatter]

16:17.109 --> 16:19.412
‐ All right, Silas.

16:19.445 --> 16:22.148
So I asked around.

16:22.181 --> 16:23.783
Nobody knows the guy.

16:23.816 --> 16:25.551
You sure it was him?

16:25.585 --> 16:27.353
‐ I'm sure.

16:27.386 --> 16:29.589
Those are the ones
that broke into my house.

16:29.622 --> 16:32.992
‐ Well, I sure would
hate to see him

16:33.025 --> 16:35.528
have an accident
out there in the dark

16:35.561 --> 16:37.263
on Purge Night.

16:37.296 --> 16:40.299
‐ I don't know.
He looks pretty clumsy to me.

16:40.333 --> 16:42.568
Might trip and shoot himself
right in the head.

16:42.602 --> 16:44.103
‐ Ladies and gentlemen,

16:44.136 --> 16:46.439
the festivities
are about to begin.

16:46.472 --> 16:49.609
Now, remember, mind the fences.

16:49.642 --> 16:51.577
They're electrified.
[laughter]

16:51.611 --> 16:55.181
You have an hour limit,
and unlike last year,

16:55.214 --> 16:57.416
trophies will be awarded.

16:57.450 --> 16:58.584
[chuckles]

16:58.618 --> 17:00.553
[applause]

17:00.586 --> 17:03.289
Now, if you'd like to follow me
to the starting line.

17:03.322 --> 17:07.059
[excited chatter]

17:07.093 --> 17:09.695
[chuckles]
All right, everyone,

17:09.729 --> 17:12.732
please remember,
be courteous

17:12.765 --> 17:15.535
and watch out
for your fellow hunters.

17:15.568 --> 17:19.038
All right, on your mark...

17:19.071 --> 17:21.908
get set...

17:21.941 --> 17:24.110
hunt!

17:24.143 --> 17:26.712
[flare fires, hisses]

17:26.746 --> 17:29.148
♪ ♪

17:29.181 --> 17:30.383
‐ Oh‐‐
‐ Faster, guys.

17:30.416 --> 17:31.984
Stay out of the light.

17:32.018 --> 17:35.087
[dark music]

17:35.121 --> 17:41.294
♪ ♪

17:41.327 --> 17:44.130
[gunshots]

17:48.167 --> 17:49.402
[computer chirping]

17:49.435 --> 17:51.103
‐ We don't want guards
at the door,

17:51.137 --> 17:52.738
so we got to give them
a reason to leave.

17:52.772 --> 17:55.641
I saw Tupac live on tour
in Tokyo last year.

17:55.675 --> 17:58.411
It was almost
as realistic as this.

17:58.444 --> 18:00.279
Boom.

18:04.183 --> 18:05.217
‐ Well, that's creepy.

18:05.251 --> 18:07.286
‐ Right now
you are walking down a street

18:07.320 --> 18:08.988
near that NFFA building,

18:09.021 --> 18:11.757
and there's absolutely no way
they can tell it's fake.

18:11.791 --> 18:13.993
‐ Wow.

18:14.026 --> 18:15.728
[chuckles]

18:15.761 --> 18:18.931
♪ ♪

18:18.965 --> 18:21.167
[computer chirps, beeps]

18:21.200 --> 18:22.602
‐ Sir, I've got another ping

18:22.635 --> 18:24.170
on Esme Carmona
three blocks away.

18:24.203 --> 18:27.440
‐ Can we confirm positive ID?
‐ Look.

18:27.473 --> 18:30.509
♪ ♪

18:30.543 --> 18:32.144
‐ That's her.

18:32.178 --> 18:33.379
Why the hell
would she show her face?

18:33.412 --> 18:35.014
‐ Sir?

18:35.047 --> 18:36.549
She's moving away.
We're gonna lose her.

18:36.582 --> 18:38.117
‐ Yeah, okay.

18:38.150 --> 18:40.252
Dispatch security.

18:40.286 --> 18:42.188
‐ Nearest team
is 15 minutes away.

18:42.221 --> 18:44.156
‐ Send them from our building.
First floor only.

18:44.190 --> 18:45.558
‐ On it.

18:45.591 --> 18:47.326
[phone line rings]

18:47.360 --> 18:49.362
‐ Hook, line, and sinker.

18:49.395 --> 18:51.464
Props to my deep‐fake ladies.
Nice work.

18:51.497 --> 18:53.165
‐ All right.
‐ All right, let's roll.

18:53.199 --> 18:57.803
♪ ♪

19:01.340 --> 19:02.008
‐ All right, ten minutes
to the bridge.

19:02.742 --> 19:04.276
Keep your eyes peeled.

19:04.310 --> 19:06.078
‐ Copy that.
‐ Hey, hey, hey.

19:06.112 --> 19:07.980
Any other hunters see us
helping the prey,

19:08.014 --> 19:09.115
they're gonna be all over us.

19:09.148 --> 19:10.750
We got to be careful.

19:10.783 --> 19:12.151
[gunshot]
‐ Oh, shit.

19:12.184 --> 19:13.753
Who's firing at us?

19:15.287 --> 19:17.723
Hey, we're hunters, too!

19:17.757 --> 19:19.625
Hold your fire!

19:19.659 --> 19:21.761
[suspenseful music]

19:21.794 --> 19:24.897
[bullets rattle]

19:24.930 --> 19:26.399
[gunshot]

19:26.432 --> 19:27.933
‐ Man, you're not
gonna believe this.

19:27.967 --> 19:29.235
It's the guy
from the plantation.

19:29.268 --> 19:31.003
‐ What?
We can't lead him to Tommy.

19:31.037 --> 19:32.438
We got to shake him.
Is he alone?

19:32.471 --> 19:34.273
‐ He's got a friend.

19:34.306 --> 19:35.875
‐ Hey, let Doug and I
draw their fire.

19:35.908 --> 19:37.510
‐ Yeah, do it
while they're reloading.

19:37.543 --> 19:38.844
Go, go, go.

19:38.878 --> 19:40.579
‐ Okay.

19:40.613 --> 19:42.581
‐ They're making
a break for it.

19:42.615 --> 19:44.183
‐ You know what?

19:44.216 --> 19:46.519
Screw the rules.

19:46.552 --> 19:49.021
‐ What is that?
Is that a tranq gun?

19:49.055 --> 19:51.624
[gunshots]

19:51.657 --> 19:56.028
♪ ♪

19:56.062 --> 19:58.764
‐ Paul? Paul?
‐ [wheezing]

19:58.798 --> 20:00.666
‐ Paul, hey.

20:00.700 --> 20:02.635
Paul?

20:02.668 --> 20:04.637
Paul?

20:04.670 --> 20:11.677
♪ ♪

20:17.817 --> 20:19.618
[door clangs]

20:19.652 --> 20:23.456
♪ ♪

20:23.489 --> 20:28.094
‐ Clint, let's drop our weapons
and finish this man‐to‐man.

20:28.127 --> 20:32.231
♪ ♪

20:32.264 --> 20:33.966
‐ Up against the wall.
Up against the wall.

20:33.999 --> 20:37.837
‐ Okay.
‐ Tuck in and don't move.

20:37.870 --> 20:39.672
Oh, shit.
All right, shh.

20:39.705 --> 20:42.074
Somebody's coming.
Fuck me.

20:42.108 --> 20:43.275
[all holler]
‐ No, thanks.

20:43.309 --> 20:44.910
‐ Oh, jeez.

20:44.944 --> 20:46.312
‐ Did you, uh‐‐
did you lose weight?

20:46.345 --> 20:48.147
‐ Oh, you obviously haven't
been skipping any meals.

20:48.180 --> 20:50.983
‐ All right, get a room.
[all chuckle]

20:51.016 --> 20:53.152
‐ [grunts]
Ah.

20:53.185 --> 20:55.187
‐ How'd he get the keys?

20:55.221 --> 20:57.890
‐ We used to be cops.

20:57.923 --> 21:00.159
‐ I can leave them on
if you want.

21:00.192 --> 21:01.894
‐ Oh, no, no,
I'm not complaining.

21:01.927 --> 21:03.829
I'm not complaining, no.
‐ Oh, thank you.

21:03.863 --> 21:05.331
Thank you.
[gunshot]

21:05.364 --> 21:06.832
‐ Go, go, go.

21:06.866 --> 21:08.234
Keep low, keep low, keep low.
‐ Go, go, go!

21:08.267 --> 21:10.302
‐ Keep moving, keep moving!

21:10.336 --> 21:12.404
[dart whizzes]
‐ [grunts]

21:12.438 --> 21:15.841
♪ ♪

21:15.875 --> 21:18.844
[high‐pitched ringing]

21:18.878 --> 21:21.580
♪ ♪

21:21.614 --> 21:22.882
[body thuds]

21:22.915 --> 21:24.049
‐ You must think
I'm a sucker, Marcus.

21:24.083 --> 21:26.619
‐ Look, Sam is inside...

21:26.652 --> 21:29.155
and he's safe.

21:29.188 --> 21:32.258
I have no intentions
on hurting anyone else.

21:32.291 --> 21:34.693
‐ You should listen to him.

21:34.727 --> 21:36.195
‐ He's lying.

21:36.228 --> 21:38.430
‐ As an act of good faith,

21:38.464 --> 21:40.065
I'll trade Sam for Clint.

21:40.099 --> 21:40.900
‐ No.
‐ We'll take it.

21:40.933 --> 21:42.168
[all murmuring]

21:42.201 --> 21:44.804
‐ He killed my wife!
You don't get to decide!

21:44.837 --> 21:47.706
‐ What happened to Maisy
was horrible...

21:47.740 --> 21:49.975
but you don't get
to endanger my husband

21:50.009 --> 21:51.310
or the rest of us.

21:51.343 --> 21:53.312
‐ No.
‐ That's right.

21:53.345 --> 21:59.752
♪ ♪

21:59.785 --> 22:02.755
‐ You said we had
to do this ourselves.

22:02.788 --> 22:04.056
♪ ♪

22:04.089 --> 22:06.058
‐ Goddamn traitors.

22:06.091 --> 22:08.861
♪ ♪

22:08.894 --> 22:12.298
All right, I'm coming in.
[gun clatters]

22:12.331 --> 22:14.233
‐ Come on.

22:14.266 --> 22:16.068
‐ [grunts]

22:16.101 --> 22:18.237
♪ ♪

22:18.270 --> 22:20.739
‐ Sam.

22:20.773 --> 22:22.474
‐ [breathing heavily]

22:22.508 --> 22:24.210
[groans]
‐ Are you okay?

22:24.243 --> 22:26.245
‐ I got you.
‐ Come on.

22:26.278 --> 22:28.814
‐ Yeah.
‐ [gasps, groans]

22:28.848 --> 22:35.788
♪ ♪

22:40.726 --> 22:42.828
[door slams]

22:44.730 --> 22:46.165
‐ A few more blocks.

22:46.198 --> 22:48.033
Should still have
a couple minutes

22:48.067 --> 22:51.103
until that
security team returns.

22:51.136 --> 22:54.039
‐ Just get me as close
to a back door as you can.

22:54.073 --> 22:56.375
♪ ♪

22:56.408 --> 22:58.978
Can you go around?
‐ Mm, yeah.

22:59.011 --> 23:00.312
♪ ♪

23:00.346 --> 23:02.348
‐ [gasps]
Careful!

23:02.381 --> 23:05.317
♪ ♪

23:05.351 --> 23:07.853
[tires squealing]

23:07.887 --> 23:10.222
[engine revving]

23:10.256 --> 23:17.296
♪ ♪

23:28.140 --> 23:28.908
‐ Thought this was
supposed to be man‐to‐man.

23:30.042 --> 23:31.810
‐ It is.

23:32.878 --> 23:33.913
‐ He's clean.

23:33.946 --> 23:36.982
‐ You've got all the guns,
and I've got none.

23:37.016 --> 23:39.351
‐ That appears to be the case.

23:40.886 --> 23:42.187
[chair clatters]

23:42.221 --> 23:43.989
Have a seat.

23:51.864 --> 23:53.933
So...

23:53.966 --> 23:55.601
how do we get past this?

23:57.369 --> 24:00.205
‐ You think
it's so fucking easy.

24:00.239 --> 24:02.808
‐ No, I don't.

24:04.310 --> 24:07.212
‐ You can never make
amends, Marcus,

24:07.246 --> 24:09.515
‐ You know, you're right.

24:09.548 --> 24:10.816
[sighs]

24:10.849 --> 24:13.886
When two people promise...

24:13.919 --> 24:17.389
to grow old together,
they should get to.

24:17.423 --> 24:19.959
And I wish...

24:19.992 --> 24:22.728
that I can change that...

24:22.761 --> 24:25.531
but I know I can't.

24:25.564 --> 24:27.866
But look, Clint...

24:27.900 --> 24:31.036
this violence...

24:31.070 --> 24:34.039
it's‐‐it's not
gonna solve anything.

24:34.073 --> 24:40.913
♪ ♪

24:44.516 --> 24:46.752
‐ They say Purging

24:46.785 --> 24:48.988
is supposed to
make you feel better.

24:49.021 --> 24:53.125
♪ ♪

24:53.158 --> 24:55.094
Nothing's gonna make me
feel better

24:55.127 --> 24:56.795
about losing Maisy.

24:56.829 --> 24:58.731
♪ ♪

24:58.764 --> 25:01.333
So what's the goddamn point?

25:01.367 --> 25:02.735
♪ ♪

25:02.768 --> 25:06.105
‐ We can start
from a clean slate...

25:06.138 --> 25:08.073
you and I.

25:08.107 --> 25:15.147
♪ ♪

25:42.408 --> 25:44.977
Thank you.
Thank you, man.

26:01.960 --> 26:03.328
Let's open the door

26:03.362 --> 26:04.997
and let them know
we worked this out.

26:05.030 --> 26:09.301
♪ ♪

26:09.334 --> 26:11.070
‐ Michelle! Michelle!

26:11.103 --> 26:13.138
‐ [screaming]

26:13.172 --> 26:15.174
[both grunting]

26:15.207 --> 26:18.043
[whimpering]

26:18.077 --> 26:20.546
‐ You took away the only person
I ever loved!

26:20.579 --> 26:23.549
‐ [grunts]
‐ So I took away yours.

26:23.582 --> 26:24.683
Do it!

26:24.716 --> 26:27.352
Purge me, motherfucker!
‐ Fuck you!

26:27.386 --> 26:28.821
‐ Do it!
You know you want to do it!

26:28.854 --> 26:30.889
‐ Watch him!

26:30.923 --> 26:33.258
‐ Marcus!
‐ [gasping]

26:33.292 --> 26:34.927
‐ Marcus!

26:34.960 --> 26:36.462
‐ Hey, baby.

26:36.495 --> 26:39.998
‐ I'm sorry.
[gasping]

26:40.032 --> 26:41.600
‐ Baby...

26:41.633 --> 26:43.569
Her lung is collapsing.

26:43.602 --> 26:46.171
Get me my medical kit
and as many towels as you can.

26:46.205 --> 26:47.506
‐ Okay, okay.
‐ It's okay, baby.

26:47.539 --> 26:49.108
It's gonna be okay.

26:49.141 --> 26:50.275
♪ ♪

26:50.309 --> 26:52.010
‐ See?

26:52.044 --> 26:55.280
It all comes out
with a little dish soap.

26:55.314 --> 26:59.585
Here, dry off your hands.
We'll be ready to go.

26:59.618 --> 27:01.286
‐ "Go"?

27:01.320 --> 27:03.422
‐ Yeah, we're gonna go out
and Purge together.

27:03.455 --> 27:06.191
Got to stay sharp.

27:06.225 --> 27:08.494
[jug shuffles]

27:08.527 --> 27:10.963
Here, have some water.

27:10.996 --> 27:12.297
♪ ♪

27:12.331 --> 27:14.366
Got to stay hydrated.

27:14.399 --> 27:16.435
Lot of hours left.

27:16.468 --> 27:18.137
♪ ♪

27:18.170 --> 27:20.305
I'm so glad we get to do this.

27:20.339 --> 27:22.407
♪ ♪

27:22.441 --> 27:24.543
Don't worry.

27:24.576 --> 27:26.545
The more you Purge,

27:26.578 --> 27:28.881
the less afraid you'll feel.

27:28.914 --> 27:31.083
Come on, drink up.

27:31.116 --> 27:34.386
♪ ♪

27:34.419 --> 27:36.421
You ready?

27:36.455 --> 27:38.390
‐ Yeah.

27:38.423 --> 27:40.125
I need‐‐I need a mask.

27:40.159 --> 27:42.394
‐ Oh, you're right.

27:42.427 --> 27:44.429
I almost forgot!

27:44.463 --> 27:47.499
Got to have one of your own.

27:47.533 --> 27:50.569
There's got to be one
in here somewhere.

27:50.602 --> 27:52.104
♪ ♪

27:52.137 --> 27:53.372
Perfect.

27:53.405 --> 27:56.408
[door opens]

27:56.441 --> 27:58.443
Son of a bitch.

27:58.477 --> 28:00.512
♪ ♪

28:00.546 --> 28:04.650
[woman screaming,
horn honking]

28:04.683 --> 28:07.653
‐ Hold on.
‐ [continues screaming]

28:07.686 --> 28:13.358
♪ ♪

28:13.392 --> 28:16.328
[muffled screaming continues]

28:16.361 --> 28:19.364
‐ [groans]

28:19.398 --> 28:26.438
♪ ♪

28:36.548 --> 28:40.319
[grunting]

28:40.352 --> 28:47.359
♪ ♪

28:51.697 --> 28:55.133
[door thuds, grunting]

28:55.167 --> 28:56.435
♪ ♪

28:56.468 --> 28:58.170
[door clatters]

28:58.203 --> 29:01.173
[indistinct shouting,
clatter in the distance]

29:01.206 --> 29:05.143
♪ ♪

29:05.177 --> 29:06.378
[groans]

29:06.411 --> 29:08.547
[panting]

29:08.580 --> 29:15.520
♪ ♪

29:15.554 --> 29:18.357
[panting]

29:18.390 --> 29:21.360
[indistinct shouting]

29:21.393 --> 29:25.030
♪ ♪

29:25.063 --> 29:29.134
[breathing heavily]

29:29.167 --> 29:36.208
♪ ♪

29:51.623 --> 29:52.224
‐ [snarls, hollers]
‐ [screams]

29:53.425 --> 29:56.361
[suspenseful music]

29:56.395 --> 29:59.898
♪ ♪

29:59.931 --> 30:01.066
[device beeps]

30:01.099 --> 30:03.769
[static crackling]

30:03.802 --> 30:06.872
[electricity humming,
devices beeping]

30:09.608 --> 30:12.778
[indistinct chatter]

30:12.811 --> 30:19.251
♪ ♪

30:19.284 --> 30:20.218
‐ Are you kidding me?

30:20.252 --> 30:22.120
‐ Please be advised...
‐ Come on.

30:22.154 --> 30:24.389
‐ The security protocols
will be disengaged

30:24.423 --> 30:26.391
during the reboot.

30:26.425 --> 30:28.393
‐ Everyone, hey, listen!

30:28.427 --> 30:30.495
Stay calm, please.

30:30.529 --> 30:32.964
The system will reboot
in 60 seconds.

30:32.998 --> 30:35.901
We're fine.

30:35.934 --> 30:38.003
[computer beeping]

30:38.036 --> 30:42.974
♪ ♪

30:43.008 --> 30:46.411
‐ [panting]
Come on.

30:46.445 --> 30:49.448
Come on, come on, come on,
come on, come on.

30:49.481 --> 30:55.220
♪ ♪

30:59.458 --> 31:02.461
[grunting]

31:05.330 --> 31:07.966
[straining]

31:07.999 --> 31:12.104
♪ ♪

31:12.137 --> 31:14.139
[generators clang,
computer beeps]

31:14.172 --> 31:16.508
[shrieking]

31:16.541 --> 31:18.043
[device beeps]

31:18.076 --> 31:20.946
[pounding on door]

31:20.979 --> 31:27.886
♪ ♪

31:27.919 --> 31:29.488
Oh, God.

31:29.521 --> 31:32.958
‐ [grunting]

31:32.991 --> 31:36.928
[indistinct shouting]

31:38.230 --> 31:41.967
‐ Oh, shit.
[women cheering]

31:42.000 --> 31:47.506
♪ ♪

31:47.539 --> 31:50.142
‐ Turner...

31:50.175 --> 31:52.177
[lights clang]

31:52.210 --> 31:56.915
♪ ♪

31:56.948 --> 31:59.618
[women shouting]

32:03.088 --> 32:06.024
[tense music]

32:06.057 --> 32:07.192
♪ ♪

32:07.225 --> 32:09.428
‐ [coughs, groans]
‐ Okay.

32:09.461 --> 32:10.529
‐ [gasping]

32:10.562 --> 32:12.564
‐ Look, there's nothing else
I can do for her here.

32:12.597 --> 32:13.865
She needs blood
and a permanent air valve.

32:13.899 --> 32:15.133
‐ The hospitals are closed.
‐ I know where to take her‐‐

32:15.167 --> 32:16.234
the triage centers.
‐ We can't just drive around

32:16.268 --> 32:17.536
all night
looking for 'em, Marcus.

32:17.569 --> 32:20.572
‐ No, it's okay.
I know where they are.

32:20.605 --> 32:22.274
They ask the doctors every year
to volunteer,

32:22.307 --> 32:23.508
and every year I say no.

32:23.542 --> 32:25.377
‐ Let me help you carry her.
‐ No, no.

32:25.410 --> 32:27.946
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
No, you guys stay here, okay?

32:27.979 --> 32:30.348
With Clint of commission,
the house is secure.

32:30.382 --> 32:31.983
Everything is safe.
‐ No, no way.

32:32.017 --> 32:34.553
‐ You really think we're gonna
let you do this alone, Marcus?

32:34.586 --> 32:36.421
‐ The only question is,
your neighbors gonna let us

32:36.455 --> 32:38.256
off this street?

32:38.290 --> 32:39.891
♪ ♪

32:39.925 --> 32:42.227
‐ We'll see about that.

32:42.260 --> 32:44.463
♪ ♪

32:44.496 --> 32:46.097
Hey!

32:46.131 --> 32:48.300
I am unarmed!

32:48.333 --> 32:52.037
I thought
I made peace with Clint...

32:52.070 --> 32:54.206
♪ ♪

32:54.239 --> 32:56.641
But he stabbed my wife
in cold blood.

32:56.675 --> 32:58.677
♪ ♪

32:58.710 --> 33:01.246
She never had anything
to do with it,

33:01.279 --> 33:03.114
but he didn't care.

33:04.616 --> 33:06.551
I had the right

33:06.585 --> 33:09.454
to purge Sam...

33:09.488 --> 33:12.157
and Clint...

33:12.190 --> 33:15.594
but I spared their lives.

33:15.627 --> 33:20.599
Now, I'm getting in‐‐
in that truck.

33:20.632 --> 33:22.100
You can stop me,

33:22.133 --> 33:26.171
but my wife's blood
is on your hands.

33:26.204 --> 33:28.273
Now here's your chance.

33:28.306 --> 33:29.975
♪ ♪

33:30.008 --> 33:32.744
You want to Purge me,
Purge me.

33:32.777 --> 33:39.985
♪ ♪

34:14.853 --> 34:17.289
[car doors close]

34:17.322 --> 34:19.157
[engine turns over]

34:19.190 --> 34:21.293
[tires squeal]

34:21.326 --> 34:27.532
♪ ♪

34:27.566 --> 34:30.101
‐ This isn't over.

34:30.135 --> 34:32.470
‐ Yes, it is.

34:32.504 --> 34:38.176
♪ ♪

34:38.209 --> 34:41.313
‐ [grunts]

34:41.346 --> 34:48.320
♪ ♪

34:48.353 --> 34:49.821
[gate rattles]

34:49.854 --> 34:52.057
‐ Turner...

34:52.090 --> 34:59.130
♪ ♪

35:32.464 --> 35:35.433
[strange whistling]

35:35.467 --> 35:40.872
♪ ♪

35:49.314 --> 35:51.783
[bell tolling in the distance]

36:09.501 --> 36:11.803
What's up, guys?

36:11.836 --> 36:15.640
[animals howling]

36:15.674 --> 36:18.309
Welcome to the party.

36:24.849 --> 36:29.954
♪ ♪

36:29.988 --> 36:31.623
Uh, hey, no...

36:31.656 --> 36:35.427
♪ ♪

36:35.460 --> 36:38.596
No, hey, hey,
I'm‐‐I'm with you.

36:38.630 --> 36:40.899
No, no, hey, look...

36:40.932 --> 36:45.170
I'm on your team.
I'm like you, see?

36:45.203 --> 36:48.940
♪ ♪

36:48.973 --> 36:51.643
It's okay.

36:51.676 --> 36:52.644
[knife slices]

36:52.677 --> 36:54.179
[grunts]

36:54.212 --> 36:55.680
[blade slides]

36:55.714 --> 36:59.350
♪ ♪

37:03.488 --> 37:03.688
‐ [grunting]

37:06.257 --> 37:09.227
[tense music]

37:09.260 --> 37:13.531
♪ ♪

37:13.565 --> 37:16.468
‐ [coughing]

37:16.501 --> 37:18.803
[coughing continues]

37:18.837 --> 37:24.309
♪ ♪

37:24.342 --> 37:26.444
‐ Now that you're awake,

37:26.478 --> 37:28.847
you can answer some questions.

37:28.880 --> 37:31.850
♪ ♪

37:31.883 --> 37:34.252
First you break into my house.

37:34.285 --> 37:36.855
Now you show up
on Purge Night.

37:36.888 --> 37:38.556
‐ [sighs]

37:38.590 --> 37:41.326
What the hell do you want
from me?

37:41.359 --> 37:43.495
‐ You were
just a random target.

37:43.528 --> 37:45.363
♪ ♪

37:45.396 --> 37:47.499
Tonight was just bad luck.

37:47.532 --> 37:50.802
♪ ♪

37:50.835 --> 37:53.338
‐ Uh‐huh.

37:53.371 --> 37:55.340
So you're telling me

37:55.373 --> 37:57.542
that my brother died
for nothing.

37:57.575 --> 38:04.582
♪ ♪

38:18.296 --> 38:20.632
Eat dirt, motherfucker.

38:20.665 --> 38:26.471
♪ ♪

38:26.504 --> 38:27.972
[phone line rings]

38:28.006 --> 38:29.741
‐ I'm in.

38:29.774 --> 38:31.476
‐ The system reboot has
everyone distracted for a bit,

38:31.509 --> 38:32.877
but you have to move fast.

38:32.911 --> 38:35.513
‐ Yeah, I'll see you in five.

38:35.547 --> 38:36.815
Better make that ten.

38:36.848 --> 38:38.716
‐ Okay.

38:38.750 --> 38:45.423
♪ ♪

38:45.456 --> 38:47.058
‐ [sniffs]

38:47.091 --> 38:49.260
[grunts]

38:49.294 --> 38:51.396
♪ ♪

38:51.429 --> 38:54.065
[gunshot]

38:54.098 --> 38:56.034
‐ Ryan!
‐ Ryan!

38:56.067 --> 38:57.635
‐ Ryan!

38:57.669 --> 38:59.003
‐ Who's got eyes on Ryan?

38:59.037 --> 39:00.638
‐ I got nothing.
‐ Me either.

39:00.672 --> 39:02.273
Ryan!

39:02.307 --> 39:06.744
♪ ♪

39:06.778 --> 39:08.446
Oh, shit.

39:08.479 --> 39:11.449
♪ ♪

39:11.482 --> 39:13.451
both: Oh.
‐ You see him?

39:13.484 --> 39:15.687
You see him?
‐ Ryan! Ryan!

39:15.720 --> 39:16.821
Right there, right there!
‐ There.

39:16.855 --> 39:19.324
‐ Ryan!
‐ There he is.

39:19.357 --> 39:21.359
‐ Grab him.
Get him on that side.

39:21.392 --> 39:23.761
‐ Be careful, be careful.
[both grunt]

39:23.795 --> 39:25.363
Pull him up!
[both grunt]

39:25.396 --> 39:26.464
Oh, shit.

39:26.497 --> 39:28.867
Ryan? Ryan?

39:28.900 --> 39:30.435
He's not breathing.
‐ Oh, fuck.

39:30.468 --> 39:32.537
‐ Turn him over on his side.
Come on.

39:32.570 --> 39:34.472
Come on.
‐ Open his mouth.

39:34.505 --> 39:36.040
‐ Ryan? Ryan?

39:36.074 --> 39:39.644
♪ ♪

39:39.677 --> 39:41.846
You're not dying
that fucking easy, Ryan!

39:41.880 --> 39:43.047
Breathe!

39:43.081 --> 39:44.883
Let's go!
‐ [coughs]

39:44.916 --> 39:48.353
‐ Oh.
‐ [coughing]

39:48.386 --> 39:50.455
‐ All right.

39:50.488 --> 39:52.590
‐ [gasps]

39:54.659 --> 39:57.328
‐ [laughs]
‐ [coughs]

39:57.362 --> 39:59.898
‐ You know, I thought you guys
came here to rescue me.

39:59.931 --> 40:03.368
[all laugh]

40:03.401 --> 40:09.440
♪ ♪

40:13.778 --> 40:14.946
‐ So what's the plan?

40:14.979 --> 40:17.015
Drive around all night
until Purge is over?

40:17.048 --> 40:18.683
‐ No, we still got work to do.

40:18.716 --> 40:20.151
‐ What are you talking about?

40:20.184 --> 40:21.386
I thought the heist was bust
'cause of Ziv?

40:21.419 --> 40:22.520
‐ Ziv's dead.

40:22.553 --> 40:25.156
I had to kill one of her guys
before Purge started.

40:25.189 --> 40:26.758
‐ Then you're dead

40:26.791 --> 40:28.626
unless we get you
out of the country tonight.

40:28.660 --> 40:30.361
‐ Not without our money.

40:30.395 --> 40:32.664
‐ And where is that?
‐ The Jackals have it.

40:32.697 --> 40:35.400
‐ The Jackals?
What the hell?

40:35.433 --> 40:37.702
‐ Ryan tipped them off.

40:37.735 --> 40:39.504
‐ Why would you do that?

40:39.537 --> 40:40.838
‐ So they would steal
the money from Ziv

40:40.872 --> 40:42.974
while we got you out of prison.

40:43.007 --> 40:44.976
‐ That's not half bad.
[laughs]

40:45.009 --> 40:47.412
I mean, it's crazy,
but I'm not complaining.

40:47.445 --> 40:49.681
‐ There's still time.
Let's go get our money.

40:49.714 --> 40:51.015
You in?

40:51.049 --> 40:53.017
‐ Let's go be thieves.

40:53.051 --> 40:54.886
♪ ♪

40:54.919 --> 40:57.188
[engine revving]

40:57.221 --> 41:01.993
♪ ♪

41:02.026 --> 41:03.528
‐ Hang in there, babe.

41:03.561 --> 41:04.696
We're almost there.
‐ She okay?

41:04.729 --> 41:06.531
‐ Look out, look out!
‐ Oh, shit.

41:06.564 --> 41:08.700
[tires screeching]

41:08.733 --> 41:10.501
‐ [gasps]

41:10.535 --> 41:12.103
[groans]
‐ Oh, shit.

41:12.136 --> 41:19.177
♪ ♪

41:22.447 --> 41:24.182
What you want to do?

41:24.215 --> 41:31.222
♪ ♪

41:31.255 --> 41:33.591
‐ Come on, come on.
He's still alive.

41:33.624 --> 41:34.993
♪ ♪

41:35.026 --> 41:37.895
All right, watch his neck.
‐ [grunts]

41:37.929 --> 41:40.798
‐ We're taking you
to a triage center.

41:40.832 --> 41:42.166
♪ ♪

41:42.200 --> 41:44.369
[both grunt]

41:44.402 --> 41:47.071
[door closes]

41:47.105 --> 41:49.774
[tires squealing]

41:49.807 --> 41:56.080
♪ ♪
